[
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(7) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Shew kindness",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".—The charge of favour to the sons of Barzillai (see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2Samuel 19:37-40",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") stands out in pleasant contrast. It has been noted that in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Jeremiah 41:17",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " there is a reference to “the habitation of Chimham,” as being “by Bethlehem,” David’s own birthplace; as if David had given him inheritance there, out of what was especially his own.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "1 Kings 2:7",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 Kings 2:7",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Show kindness to the sons of Barzillai ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— David’s gratitude here expressed is remarkable. Barzillai only desired him to show kindness to Chimham, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Samuel 19:37",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; but he extends it to all his sons. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Let them be of those that eat at thy table ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— As Mephibosheth had done at David’s table. It is probable Mephibosheth was now dead, for otherwise David would not have forgotten him. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "For so they came to me ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Such kindness they showed me; inviting him to Barzillai’s house, who sustained him in his great distress, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Samuel 19:32",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "2:5-11 These dying counsels concerning Joab and Shimei, did not come from personal anger, but for the security of Solomon's throne, which was the murders he had committed, but would readily repeat them to carry any purpose; though long reprieved, he shall be reckoned with at last. Time does not wear out the guilt of any sin, particularly of murder. Concerning Shimei, Hold him not guiltless; do not think him any true friend to thee, or thy government, or fit to be trusted; he has no less malice now than he had then. David's dying sentiments are recorded, as delivered under the influence of the Holy Ghost,",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Barnes' Notes on the Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "One of the sons of Barzillai here intended was probably Chimham (see the margin reference). Who the others were is not known. The family continued down to the return from the captivity, and still held property in Israel (compare ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ezra 2:61",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Nehemiah 7:63",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "6. Do … according to thy wisdom—Joab's immense popularity with the army required that any proceedings instituted against him should be taken with great prudence and deliberation.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Poole's Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Quest.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Why doth he not require the like kindness to Mephibosheth the son of his dear Jonathan? ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Answ.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Either he and his were now extinct, or by their after-miscarriages had forfeited his favour. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "For so, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " i.e. with such kindness either as I cannot express, (as the particle so is elsewhere used,) or as I command thee to show to them. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "They, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " i.e. Barzillai and his sons; for though Barzillai only be mentioned, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bldvs",
        "text": " 2 Samuel 17:27",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Samuel 17:27",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", yet his sons doubtless were instrumental in the business, especially Chimham, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bldvs",
        "text": " 2 Samuel 19:37,38",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Samuel 19:37",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ",38",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "But show kindness to the sons of Barzillai the Gileadite,.... Who perhaps was now dead, and therefore he would have kindness shown to his posterity for his sake: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and let them be of those that eat of thy table; as Mephibosheth had at his, who also perhaps was dead, since no notice is taken of him; and as David would have had Barzillai, but he desired to be excused on account of his age: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "for so they came to me, when I fled because of thy brother, Absalom; that is, they came to him, not only Barzillai, but his sons it seems; and fed him or furnished him with provisions, when he was obliged to fly to the other side Jordan, because of the rebellion of his son Absalom. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "for so they came to me, when I fled because of thy brother, Absalom; that is, they came to him, not only Barzillai, but his sons it seems; and fed him or furnished him with provisions, when he was obliged to fly to the other side Jordan, because of the rebellion of his son Absalom. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Geneva Study Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cverse2",
        "text": "But shew kindness unto the sons of Barzillai the Gileadite, and let them be of those that eat at thy table: {f} for so they came to me when I fled because of Absalom thy brother.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "But shew kindness unto the sons of Barzillai the Gileadite, and let them be of those that eat at thy table: ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "cverse3",
            "text": "{f}",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " for so they came to me when I fled because of Absalom thy brother.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(f) That is, they dealt mercifully with me.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Cambridge Bible for Schools and Colleges",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "sons of Barzillai the Gileadite",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] The deserving conduct of Barzillai, during David’s flight from Absalom, is narrated ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Samuel 19:31",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "seqq",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The Chimham there mentioned was probably a son of Barzillai, though we are not expressly told so. No other son is anywhere spoken of, but we find that Barzillai had daughters (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ezra 2:61",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Nehemiah 7:63",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") and he probably was father of a large family. Barzillai, at his advanced age, would not come alone to conduct David over Jordan, and though he only commends one person to the king’s attention there may have been several sons in his retinue.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "of",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " those ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "that eat at thy table",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] A common mode in Eastern countries of shewing regard. Thus Mephibosheth, Jonathan’s son, was provided for at David’s table (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Samuel 9:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Samuel 9:10-11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), and such treatment put the recipient in a position like that of the king’s sons.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "for so they came to me",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] i.e. With kind acts and generous supplies of food when I was in great need. Let their reward be of a similar nature.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 7.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "And to the sons of Barzillai",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " [the \"Beni-Barzillai\" would include son, or sons, and all other descendants. It is highly probable, though it is not expressly stated, that Chimham was the son of Bar-zillai (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Samuel 19:37",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Rawlinson says, \"Who the other sons were is not known.\" It would be more correct to say that we do not know whether there were any other sons. The family was still existing ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "temp.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Ezra (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ezra 2:61",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), where, it is worth noticing, we read of the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "daughters",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " of Barzillai (cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Nehemiah 7:63",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). In ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Jeremiah 41:17",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", we read of the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "\"habitation",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "hebrew",
        "text": "גֵּדוּת",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", caravanserai, khan) of Chemoham,\" where the Keri has Chimham. It has been argued from the mention of this name, and the fact that their khan was near Bethlehem, that David or Solomon gave the family land there], ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "and let them be of those that eat at thy table",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " [",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "i.e.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", of those who have their sustenance from the royal table, not necessarily at it (Keil); cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Daniel 1:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Kings 25:29",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Presence ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "at",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " the table is expressed by ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "hebrew",
        "text": "עַל שֻׂלְחָן",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Samuel 11, 12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). It was esteemed an essential part of royal munificence throughout the East that the king should feed a large number of retainers and dependants. Cf. the account of Solomon's daffy provision in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 4:22, 23",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; also ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Samuel 19:28",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Judges 1:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "]; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "for so",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " [",
        "children": []
