        "text": "קָרַב",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " often includes, as here, the idea of succour. Cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 69:19",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Lamentations 3:57",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Barzillai certainly came (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Samuel 17:27",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), and probably Chimham, but the Speaker's Commentary is mistaken when it says that \"Chimham is mentioned as present.\" He was present at the return of David (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Samuel 19:31, 38",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", but not necessarily before] ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "when I fled because of",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " [lit., \"from the face of \"] ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Absalom",
        "children": []
