    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "If the demands of justice required that Joab should be punished, the duty of gratitude was no less holy to the dying king. And Solomon was to show this to the sons of Barzillai the Gileadite, and make them companions of his table; because Barzillai had supplied David with provisions on his flight from Absalom (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Samuel 17:27",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "., ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Samuel 19:32",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".). שׁלחנך בּאכלי והיוּ, \"let them be among those eating of thy table;\" i.e., not, \"let them draw their food from the royal table,\" - for there was no particular distinction in this, as all the royal attendants at the court received their food from the royal kitchen, as an equivalent for the pay that was owing - but, \"let them join in the meals at the royal table.\" The fact that in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Samuel 9:10-11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Samuel 9:13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", we have על־שׁלחן אכל to express this, makes no material difference. According to ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Samuel 19:38",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", Barzillai had, it is true, allowed only one son to follow the king to his court. \"For so they drew near to me,\" i.e., they showed the kindness to me of supplying me with food; compare ",
        "children": []
      },
